HEADWORD: Mastigure
<hw>Mas"ti*gure</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ma`stix</grk>, <grk>ma`stigos</grk>, a scourge + <?/ tail.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several large spiny-tailed lizards of
the genus <gen>Uromastix</gen>. They inhabit Southern Asia and North
Africa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

